Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section Y CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

yannisgr Greek fonts by Yannis Haralambous.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
yfonts No caption.
A LaTeX interface to the old-german fonts designed by Yannis Haralambous: Gotisch, Schwabacher, Fraktur and the baroque initials.
license: unknown (1999/01/27)
yhmath Extended maths fonts for LaTeX.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
yi4latex No caption.
Package to provide support in LaTeX for writing all standardized Yi characters. Yi (also known as Lolo) is spoken in Southern China; the script is syllabic, based on an older, ideographic system.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
yinit No caption.
A special font (yinit) is defined to be used for initial dropped capitals.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
youngtab Typeset Young-Tableaux.
A package for typesetting Young-Tableaux, mathematical symbols for the representations of groups, providing two macros, \yng(1) and \young(1) to generate the whole Young-Tableaux.
license: lppl version: 1.1 (1999/05/20)
yplan Daily planner type calendar.
Prints two six-monthly vertrical-type daily planner (i.e., months along the top, days downwards), with each 6-month period fitting onto a single A4 (or US letter) sheet. Updated annually.
license: lppl (1999/05/06)
ytex Macro package developed at MIT.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
